data.meta_description: January 27, 1805: Born, Princesses Sophie and Maria Anna of Bavaria. The identical twin sisters were the daughters of King Maximilian I of Bavaria and his second wife, Caroline of Baden. Sophie married Franz Karl, Archduke of Austria, and was the mother of Franz Joseph I of Austria and Maximilian I of Mexico. Maria Anna married Frederick Augustus II of of Saxony. (That's Maria Anna on the left; Sophie on the right.)
